The White House has issued a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo will continue. This national emergency was declared by President Obama in 2006 and involves measures blocking the property of certain individuals contributing to the conflict in the country. The situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo is characterized by widespread violence and atrocities that threaten regional stability. The national emergency and the measures adopted to address it will remain in effect for another year.